runs.comm: around the wicket, goes to flick to leg and misses, cry for lbw but it pitched well outside leg
yorker-length dug out, Hales jams the bat down on it but it's got enough pace to run all the way up to the straight boundary
low full toss but Hales can only turn it to square leg
full deliver driven to mid-off for a quick single
full delivery on the stumps, beautifully threaded through the covers, decent timing but Seelaar runnings back dives and saves superbly
full on the stumps, flicked back to the bowler
just short of a length at the hip, turned down to long leg
pulled well wide of off stump
good length at the body, dropped into midwicket for a quick single
punched straight from the crease, mid-off's dive isn't enough to stop it completely and they get back for a couple
length on leg stump, clipped to short long leg, too quickly for the single, not a great line with that man up in the circle
fuller and sliding across Lumb who swings and misses
yorker-length, dug out to mid-on
good length, firm drive well saved at extra-cover
back of a length and wide enough for Hales to steer it through the three fielders behind square on the off side, excellent timing
short ball and Hales is through with the hook too soon and misses
another sharp forcing shot on the off side, point saves very well but can't gather cleanly and they get a run
length ball on off stump, guided to backward point

touch fuller and Lumb drives in the air and picks out cover a similar dismissal to the South Africa game, not picking the gap on the off side. It was timed well but at shoulder height and presented an easy catch
firm drive from just outside off to cover on the edge of the circle
similar stroke finds the same fielder
slower ball on a similar full length, forward comes Hales steering this to backward point
yorker-length which Hales tries to dig out from just outside off stump and missed
shorter and Hales tries to pull but can only steer this to short long leg
drive which squirts off a thick outside edge in the air but wide of backward point and down to third man for a single

length ball, pulled, missed and it's bowled him! Just clipping the off bail on the way through. Hales struggling in tougher batting conditions, trying to force the pace - the length was not there to pull - and has fallen
full sliding wide of off stump, left alone
tighter line and makes Morgan play at this and beats him outside off
slightly wider line that Morgan leaves alone
on the stumps this time, Morgan tries to turn it to leg and gets struck on the pad
good line and length again, Morgan plays with soft hands and manages to run it down fine of third man so they get back for two
good length at the off stump, Moeen angles it to backward point
full length driven at outside off and gets a thick outside edge down to third man
just full of a good length on off stump, Morgan forward to play into the covers
Morgan steps across the stumps and takes a full length delivery through midwicket with excellent timing

this is pushed wider of off stump and Morgan drives off a good length and edges to slip! England lose a third here! So disciplined outside off stump so far but Netherlands have probed that line and here got their rewards. The slip was pushed wider to about a third slip and he pouched an easy chance at thigh height! Game on
good length wide of off stump, left alone
full and wide of off stump, Moeen reaches for it and steers it to cover
good length and a tighter line, angled out to point
fuller and driven to deep cover
full length a foot wide of off stump, a firm drive to extra cover
touch shorter and Buttler tries to cut and misses
a step down the track and flicks to the leg side, getting a single in front of mid-on
full length, flicked to short midwicket where there's a sharp save
full length again on the stumps, flicked to the same fielder
back of a length, slightly more angled across Buttler who tucks it to point
a little too leg stump and it takes the pad down towards long leg, wide enough of the fielder for a second
middle and leg line, flicked out to deep midwicket
full just outside off and driven firmly down to long-off

full and wide of off stump, Moeen drives at it and slaps it to cover! Another one down and England are in trouble here. A slow offcutter from Borren, Moeen has greedily seen some width to work with, gone for a big drive and got it off the toe of the bat straight to the fielder
just short of a length, steered to point
wider of off stump and turned down to third man
forward and turned into midwicket, the deep fielder has to sprint in and can't save two
step to the off side and flicks a full ball out to deep square leg
forward just outside off, dropped into cover for a quick single
just short of a length, Bopara goes to turn it to leg, gets struck on the thigh pad and they take a quick single
Buttler across his stumps to scoop and missed it complete, good job the line was wide of off stump
short and pulled into the leg side, no timing and it lands well in front of deep midwicket
overpitched outside off, slashed away through point and Cooper on the rope does well to save four
low full toss ran to mid-off, the take on the fielder easily

short ball, Buttler swings into the deep, again mistimes the stroke and picks out deep midwicket another big strike for Netherlands. Slower ball out of the back of the hand, Buttler was aiming big to the leg side and simply got it nowhere near the meat of the bat, pretty mindless batting really
this slides down the leg side
and again
tossed up outside off, Bopara drives hard to cover who can't save properly
back to cut off off stump and finds cover
firm drive through cover and they're able to get back for the second
blocked in the crease towards point
full just outside off, driven hard a touch wide of long-off and that's the invitation for them to come back for the second
another drive, this straight to extra-cover
firm drive back to the bowler and dropped! What a chance to remove England's king pin here. Firm chance to the bowler's left he got two hands to it but it bounced straight out
full on the stumps, flicked out to deep midwicket and the fifty comes up, goodness
a little too straight and flicked down to long leg

slower ball ends up a full toss, he pulls it out to deep square leg, for some reason they're coming back for second and Bresnan is miles out!! Oh my word what absolute carnage! Bopara was scooting back for the second and would have got home easily but Bresnan was so slow and ended up yards short of his ground
firm drive out to deep cover
slower ball on the stumps, turned into midwicket and they take one
leg stump and full, flicked down to long leg
full delivery, flicked out towards deep square leg, no second run there
full length a foot wide of off stump, driven steadily down to mid-off
full on the leg stump, clipped out through square leg for an easy run
forward and just pressed back to the bowler
Jordan plays across this a little and there's a cry for lbw, not out given, big inside edge onto the front pad
slow offcutter on the stumps, turned through square leg, just a single and singles are starting to be more than okay for Netherlands
overpitched and driven hard to extra cover who dives and fumbles and they take a single
legcutter this time, ran out to deep cover
low full toss just panned down to long-off
another low full toss, clipped to long-on this time, wide enough for a couple
forward and runs a full ball to the edge of the circle on the leg side, all the fielders there out on the rope so they get back for two again
Bopara dancing on the crease can only find the bowler
swept out to deep midwicket, just the single
driven from outside off, they charge for three as deep cover has a long way to run to his right, but Jordan didn't fancy a third
full delivery driven down to long-off
tried to be swung down the ground but again the timing is totally not there and it's on several bounces to long-off
pushed from the crease through the covers

length ball swung over the leg side, deep midwicket is right back on the rope and takes the catch!! Huge wicket and surely England are dead and buried now! The catch taken inches from the rope, Seelaar holds on solidly and the Netherlands are dancing about, that could well be the game
length outside off, Jordan swings to the off side and gets a bottom edge up the wicket
short and pulled straight to deep midwicket
leg stump, turned to deep midwicket

full length outside off stump, Jordan swings it down the ground but gets nowhere near enough bat on it, long-off is running in, dives forward and takes the catch! Another piece of top fielding from the Dutch and this game is all but theirs now! Once again, an England batsman is not able to time the ball properly in this innings
full just outside off, slapped hard down the ground but long-off can cut it off
full delivery, pushed carefully to cover
down the track, aims leg side, it comes off a huge top edge and whirls over point and will run away for four! Finally England find the rope
length outside off, slapped down to long-off
length, Broad swings to leg and gets it off an outside edge to short third man, they sprint a run
down the track again but can only run this to long-off
slower ball, huge swing to leg and Broad misses
low full toss outside off, slapped only to deep cover

length ball wide of off stump, Broad aims a swing leg side and nicks it through to the keeper! England's last faint hope walks off. He had to try something, aimed a mighty whack to leg, got there too soon and feathered an edge behind
low full toss flicked out to deep midwicket

swing over the off side, it loops just over cover and Tredwell survives but oh my word there's a mix up mid-pitch and there's a run out!! And that will finish things off!!! What a calamitous way to end and it sums England's batting performance up, Parry totally stranded in the middle of the wicket
